==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Preceptor
<hw>Pre*cep"tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>praeceptor</ets>, fr. <ets>praecipere</ets> to teach: cf. F.
<ets>pr⟦eacute⟧cepteur</ets>. See <er>Precept</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>One who gives commands, or makes rules; specifically, the master or
principal of a school; a teacher; an instructor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The head of a preceptory among the Knights
Templars.</def> <rj><au>Sir W. Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Preceptorial</ent>⟦br⟧
